atus=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319004538/http://www.cordobacf.com/-/comunicado-ofic-38 |archivedate=19 March 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]]\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Ignacio Mart\u00ednez]]\n| Sacked\n| 5 April 2015<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.udalmeriasad.com/-/el-almeria-decide-destituir-a-juan-ignacio-martinez-como-entrenador-del-primer-equipo |title=El Almer\u00eda decide destituir a Juan Ignacio Mart\u00ednez como entrenador del primer equipo |work=Almer\u00eda's official website |date=5 April 2015 |accessdate=5 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407222112/http://www.udalmeriasad.com/-/el-almeria-decide-destituir-a-juan-ignacio-martinez-como-entrenador-del-primer-equipo |archivedate= 7 April 2015 }}</ref>\n| 18th\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Sergi Barju\u00e1n]]\n| 6 April 2015<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.udalmeriasad.com/-/sergi-barjuan-es-el-nuevo-entrenador-del-almeria-por-lo-que-resta-de-temporada |title=Sergi Barjuan es el nuevo entrenador del Almer\u00eda por lo que resta de temporada |work=Almer\u00eda's official website |date=6 April 2015 |accessdate=6 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150408232020/http://www.udalmeriasad.com/-/sergi-barjuan-es-el-nuevo-entrenador-del-almeria-por-lo-que-resta-de-temporada |archivedate= 8 April 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n|- \n| [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]]\n| {{flagicon|Spain}} [[V\u00edctor Fern\u00e1ndez]]\n| Sacked\n| 8 April 2015\n| 17th\n| {{flagicon|Spain}} [[V\u00edctor S\u00e1nchez]]\n| 8 April 2015\n|-\n| [[Granada CF|Granada]]\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Abel Resino]]\n| Sacked\n| 1 May 2015<ref>{{cite news |title=El Granada destituye a Abel Resino |url=http://www.marca.com/2015/05/01/futbol/equipos/granada/1430470930.html |work=Marca |date=1 May 2015 |accessdate=1 May 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| 19th\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00f3n Sandoval]]\n| 1 May 2015<ref>{{cite news|url=http://granadacf.ideal.es/noticias/201505/01/granada-firma-jose-ramon-20150501153438.html|title=El Granada CF ficha a Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00f3n Sandoval hasta final de temporada|work=Ideal.es|date=1 May 2015|accessdate=1 May 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Overview==\nOn 2 May, C\u00f3rdoba were relegated with three games left to play in the season, after losing 0\u20138 at home against Barcelona.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cordoba 0 Barcelona 8: Suarez nets hat-trick as hosts are relegated|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/cordoba-0-barcelona-8-suarez-nets-hat-trick-hosts-are-relegated|accessdate=4 May 2015|work=[[Four Four Two]]|date=2 May 2015}}</ref> Eight days later, Villarreal confirmed sixth place and an entry into the [[UEFA Europa League]] with [[Joel Campbell]]'s winning goal against Elche.<ref>{{cite news|title=Villarreal head into Europa League|url=http://www.marca.com/en/2015/05/10/en/football/spanish_football/1431282094.html|accessdate=18 May 2015|work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|date=10 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nBarcelona, playing with a three-man attack of [[Lionel Messi]], [[Neymar]] and [[Luis Su\u00e1rez]] under new manager [[Luis Enrique (footballer)|Luis Enrique]],<ref name=west>{{cite news|last1=West|first1=Andy|title=Barcelona win La Liga: 10 key factors behind their revival|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32752159|accessdate=18 May 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=17 May 2015}}</ref> won the title on 17 May with a goal by Messi to defeat holders Atl\u00e9tico Madrid at the [[Vicente Calder\u00f3n Stadium]]. It came exactly a year after Atl\u00e9tico had won their league title at Barcelona's [[Camp Nou]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Atl Madrid 0-1 Barcelona|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32757176|accessdate=18 May 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=17 May 2015}}</ref> Real Madrid, with profound inconsistency in the second half of the season,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/real-madrid/story/2461558/ancelotti-wants-to-keep-madrid-job-but-prepared-for-sacking|title=Carlo Ancelotti wants to keep Real Madrid job but prepared for dismissal|publisher=}}</ref> secured second place on the same day as Barcelona won the title, with a 1\u20134 win at Espanyol.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McMath|first1=James|title=Espanyol 1-4 Real Madrid|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32757183|accessdate=18 May 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=17 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe battle for the Champions League was settled in the last ten minutes of the season. Valencia, in fourth place with 74 points, went into the last match of the season at relegation-threatened Almer\u00eda, facing all three possibilities of direct qualification to the group stage of the Champions League, qualification to the play-off round, or missing out on the Champions League altogether. Valencia won the match 3\u20132 to secure fourth place, as Atl\u00e9tico Madrid, three points ahead, drew at Granada. Sevilla, with a 3\u20132 win at M\u00e1laga, achieved a record 76 points total without Champions League qualification, finishing fifth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/spanish-primera-division/match/402257/almeria-valencia/report|title=Almeria 2-3 Valencia|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/spanish-primera-division/match/402249/granada-atletico-madrid/report|title=Granada stay up thanks to draw|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/spanish-primera-division/match/402256/malaga-sevilla-fc/report|title=Malaga 2-3 Sevilla FC|publisher=}}</ref> Sevilla however qualified for the Champions League by winning the [[2015 UEFA Europa League Final]]. \n\nEarlier in the season, on 7 February, Atl\u00e9tico Madrid achieved a 4-0 victory over city rivals Real Madrid. It was Real's biggest loss since a 5-0 loss to Barcelona in November 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2015/02/10/atletico-madrid-real-rout-tactics-la-liga-simeone-ancelotti|title=Atletico Madrid finds another gear in demolition of Real Madrid|publisher=SI.com}}</ref> \n\nDespite finishing the season in the 13th position, on 5 June, Elche was relegated to Segunda Divisi\u00f3n due to its financial struggles.<ref name=\"Elche\">{{cite web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/news/official-statement-27|title=Official statement|publisher=LFP.es|date=5 June 2015}}</ref> Newcomers [[SD Eibar|Eibar]], who finished the season in the 18th position, will take Elche's place in [[2015\u201316 La Liga]].\n\n==League table==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://www.ligabbva.com/3176_clasificacion/index.html La Liga]\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team1=BAR |team2=RMA |team3=ATM |team4=VAL |team5=SEV |team6=VIL |team7=ATH |team8=CEL |team9=MLG |team10=ESP |team11=RVA |team12=RSO |team13=ELC |team14=LEV |team15=GET |team16=DEP |team17=GRA |team18=EIB |team19=ALM |team20=COR\n\n|hth_ESP=Espanyol ahead on head-to-head record; Rayo Vallecano\u2013Espanyol 1\u20133, Espanyol\u2013Rayo Vallecano 1\u20131.\n|hth_RVA=ESP\n|hth_LEV=Levante ahead on head-to-head record; Levante\u2013Getafe 1\u20131, Getafe\u2013Levante 0\u20131.\n|hth_GET=LEV\n|hth_DEP=Head-to-head record: Deportivo 7 pts, Granada 6 pts, Eibar 2 pts\n|hth_GRA=DEP\n|hth_EIB=DEP\n|note_ELC=Elche administratively relegated by the LFP.<ref name=\"Elche\"/>\n|note_ALM=Almer\u00eda was docked 3 points due to an unpayment of a transfer.<ref name=\"Almeria2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.superdeporte.es/futbol/2015/05/27/almeria-retira-recurso-acaba-liga/258833.html|publisher=SuperDeporte|date=27 May 2015|accessdate=15 January 2017|title=El Almer\u00eda retira el recurso y acaba la Liga con 29 puntos}}</ref>\n\n<!--Update team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1=CLGS |result2=CLGS |result3=CLGS |result4=CLPO |result5=CLGS |result6=ELGS |result7=EL3Q |result13=REL |result19=REL |result20=REL\n\n<!--Update team results here and then (if needed positions above). Dont forget to 