id]]\n|name_RSO=[[Real Sociedad]]\n|name_SEV=[[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]]\n|name_VAL=[[Valencia CF|Valencia]]\n|name_VIL=[[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]\n\n<!--Table settings and rules-->\n|show_limit=5\n|class_rules = 1) points; 2) head-to-head points; 3) head-to-head goal difference; 4) goal difference; 5) number of goals scored; 6) fair-play points; 7) playoff match<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lnfs.es/Data/Adjuntos/1.3%20RFEF%20%20Reglamento%20General%202014-2015.pdf|title=Reglamento General|publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]]|trans-title=General Regulations|format=PDF|access-date=26 March 2015|website=www.[[LNFS|lnfs]].es|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n<!--Qualification and relegation column definitions-->\n|res_col_header=QR\n|col_CLGS=green1 |text_CLGS=Qualification to [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|UEFA Champions League group stage]]\n|col_CLPO=green2 |text_CLPO=Qualification to [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League#Play-off round|UEFA Champions League play-off round]]\n|col_ELGS=blue1  |text_ELGS=Qualification to [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League#Group stage|UEFA Europa League group stage]]\n|col_EL3Q=blue2  |text_EL3Q=Qualification to [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League#Third qualifying round|UEFA Europa League third qualifying round]]\n|col_REL=red1    |text_REL=Relegation to [[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]]\n\n|note_res_CLGS=[[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] qualified for the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|Champions League group stage]] by winning the [[2014\u201315 UEFA Europa League]]. As a result, the fifth-placed spot for the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League#Group stage|Europa League group stage]] they earned was vacated without replacement as per UEFA regulations.\n|note_res_ELGS=Since the winners of the [[2014\u201315 Copa del Rey]], [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], qualified for European competition based on league position, the spot awarded to the cup winners ([[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League#Group 