ns League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]<br>[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]<br>[[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]<br>[[Valencia CF|Valencia]]<br>[[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] (as [[2015 UEFA Europa League Final|Europa League champions]])\n| continentalcup2    = [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]<br>[[Athletic Bilbao]]\n| league topscorer   = [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]<br>(48 goals)<ref name=\"topscorer\"/>\n| best goalkeeper    = [[Claudio Bravo (footballer)|Claudio Bravo]]<br>(0.51 goals/match)\n| biggest home win   = {{nobreak|[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] 9\u20131 [[Granada CF|Granada]]}}<br />(5 April 2015)\n| biggest away win   = {{nobreak|[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]] 0\u20138 [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]}}<br />(2 May 2015)\n| highest scoring    = {{nobreak|[[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] 2\u20138 [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]}}<br />(20 September 2014)<br />{{nobreak|[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] 9\u20131 [[Granada CF|Granada]]}}<br />(5 April 2015)<br />{{nobreak|[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] 7\u20133 [[Getafe CF|Getafe]]}}<br />(23 May 2015)\n| matches            = 380\n| total goals        = 1009\n| longest wins       = 12 matches<ref name=\"stattostatistics\">{{cite web |url=http://www.statto.com/football/stats/spain/primera-division/2014-2015/longest-sequences/full |title=Spanish Primera Division 2014\u201315 |publisher=statto.com |accessdate=22 April 2015}}</ref><br />[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]\n| longest unbeaten   = 14 matches<ref name=\"stattostatistics\"/><br />[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n| longest winless    = 20 matches<ref name=\"stattostatistics\"/><br />[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]]\n| longest losses     = 10 matches<ref name=\"stattostatistics\"/><br />[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]]\n| highest attendance = 98,760<ref name=stats>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/spanish-primera-division/15/statistics/performance |title=Spanish Primera Divisi\u00f3n Statistics \u2013 2014\u201315 |work=ESPN FC |publisher=Entertainment and Sports Programming Network (ESPN) |accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><br />[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] 2\u20131 [[Real Madrid]]<br />(22 March 2015)\n| lowest attendance  = 3,500<ref name=\"stats\"/><br />[[Getafe CF|Getafe]] 2\u20131 [[Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]]<br />(26 January 2015)\n| attendance         = 10,161,726<ref name=\"stats\"/>\n| average attendance = 26,741<ref name=\"stats\"/>\n| prevseason = [[2013\u201314 La Liga|2013\u201314]]\n| nextseason = [[2015\u201316 La Liga|2015\u201316]]\n}}\nThe '''2014\u201315 [[La Liga]]''' season (known as the ''Liga BBVA'' for sponsorship reasons) was the 84th season of the premier [[association football]] league in Spain. The campaign began on 23 August 2014 and ended on 24 May 2015.\n\n[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] won its 23rd title on 17 May 2015 after defeating defending champions [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] at the [[Vicente Calder\u00f3n Stadium]], and also equalled the all-time record goal difference of +89 (110 goals scored and 21 conceded), originally set by [[Real Madrid]] in the [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]] season.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/may/17/atletico-madrid-barcelona-la-liga-match-report|title=Barcelona clinch title with Lionel Messi magic against Atl\u00e9tico Madrid|date=17 May 2015|work=Guardian|accessdate=19 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/barcelona/11611738/Lionel-Messi-hands-Barcelona-23rd-La-Liga-title.html|title=Lionel Messi hands Barcelona 23rd La Liga title|date=17 May 2015|work=Daily Telegraph|accessdate=19 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Teams==\n===Promotion and relegation (pre-season)===\nA total of 20 teams contest the league, including 17 sides from the [[2013\u201314 La Liga|2013\u201314 season]] and three promoted from the [[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]]. This includes the two top teams ([[SD Eibar|Eibar]] and [[Real Club Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]]) from the Segunda Divisi\u00f3n, and the winner of the  [[2014 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n play-offs|play-offs]], [[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]].\n\n[[SD Eibar|Eibar]] became the first club from Segunda Divisi\u00f3n to achieve promotion to La Liga after its 1\u20130 victory over [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|Alav\u00e9s]] on 25 May 2014. Eibar made their La Liga debut in the 2014\u201315 season.<ref>[http://www.goal.com/en-sg/news/3882/spain/2014/05/26/4840739/eibar-seal-stunning-promotion-to-la-liga Eibar seal stunning promotion to La Liga]; Goal.com, 26 May 2014</ref>\n\n[[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] won promotion back to La Liga after one season in Segunda Divisi\u00f3n with a 1\u20130 victory over [[Real Ja\u00e9n]] on 31 May 2014.<ref>[http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/deportivo-la-coruna/result/result-deportivo-promoted-to-la-liga_157753.html Result: Deportivo La Coruna promoted to La Liga]; SportsMole, 31 May 2014</ref>\n\n[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]] won the promotion play-off against [[UD Las Palmas|Las Palmas]] and returned to the top level after 42 years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Las Palmas-Cordoba La Liga play-off ends with pitch invasion|url=http://www.goal.com/en-india/news/138/spain/2014/06/23/4905144/las-palmas-cordoba-la-liga-play-off-ends-with-pitch-invasion|accessdate=30 June 2014|publisher=Goal.com|date=23 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Stadia and locations===\n{{Location map+ |Spain |width=450 |float=right |caption=Location of teams in '''2014\u201315 La Liga''' |places=\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=36.840028 |long=-2.435436 |label=<small>[[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=43.264283 |long=-2.950153 |label=<small>[[Athletic Bilbao]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=40.401703 |long=-3.720628 |label=<small>[[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid|Atl\u00e9tico&nbsp;Madrid]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=41.380889 |long=2.1228167 |label=<small>[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]</small> |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=37.872219 |long=-4.764550 |label=<small>[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=42.211842 |long=-8.739706 |label=<small>[[Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=43.368717 |long=-8.417514 |label=<small>[[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=43.181706 |long=-2.475803 |label=<small>[[SD Eibar|Eibar]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=38.267111 |long=-0.663272 |label=<small>[[Elche CF|Elche]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=41.347861 |long=2.0756667 |label=<small>[[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=40.325728 |long=-3.714950 |label=<small>[[Getafe CF|Getafe]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=37.152925 |long=-3.595744 |label=<small>[[Granada CF|Granada]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=39.494703 |long=-0.363842 |label=<small>[[Levante UD|Levante]]</small>}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=36.734217 |long=-4.426603 |label=<small>[[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=40.391828 |long=-3.658586 |label=<small>[[Rayo Vallecano|Rayo&nbsp;Vallecano]]</small> |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=40.453053 |long=-3.688356 |label=<small>[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=43.301364 |long=-1.973536 |label=<small>[[Real Sociedad]]</small> |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=37.384039 |long=-5.970583 |label=<small>[[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat=39.474616 |long=-0.358219 |label=<small>[[Valencia CF|Valencia]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Spain |lat